secution and escape to Holland where she was betrayed, the horrors of life in the Westerbork and Bergen-Belsen camps, and her eventual flight via "Transport 222" to Palestine. Written immediately after her liberation in 1944, this unique document captures a little-known chapter of Holocaust history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aJewish refugeeszPalestine. 0aJewsxPersecutionszGermanyzJever. 0aJewsxPersecutionszNetherlandszGroningen. 0aTransport 222, 1944. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xJewsxRescue. 7aHISTORY / Holocaust.2bisacsh  aAuschwitz.  aBergen-Belsen.  aGerman invasion of the Netherlands.  aHolocaust.  aTransport 22.  aWesterbork.  aantisemitic persecution.1 aBerlina, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeters, Hartmut, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076741408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022 Englishz978311099296008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022z9783110992939oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644699096?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644699096423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781644699096/original  a978-3-11-076700-1  DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076741-4  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099296-0  EBOOK PACKAGE H